@page "/samples"
@inject IJSRuntime JS
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>Prompt Templates — Qwen TTS</PageTitle>

<div class="main-content">
    <div class="top-bar">
        <div class="top-bar-brand"><span>📋</span> Prompt Templates</div>
        <div class="top-bar-actions">
            <a href="/" class="nav-pill">🔊 TTS</a>
            <a href="/podcast" class="nav-pill">🎙️ Podcast</a>
            <a href="/samples" class="nav-pill active">📋 Prompts</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.88rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Copy these prompts into ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, or any LLM to generate podcast scripts in the correct format for the Podcast Generator.
    </p>

    <!-- Claude Research Template -->
    <div class="tts-card">
        <div class="prompt-header">
            <h3>🔎 Research-Based — Claude / LLM with web access</h3>
            <button class="copy-btn" @onclick='() => CopyToClipboard("prompt-research")'>📋 Copy</button>
        </div>
        <p class="prompt-desc">Best for LLMs that can research topics (Claude with web search, ChatGPT with browsing, Perplexity). The LLM researches the topic first, then generates the script and offers it as a downloadable file.</p>
        <div class="prompt-box" id="prompt-research">Generate a podcast conversation script between two hosts about the topic that you researched.

Rules:
- Use exactly this format for each segment (the --- separator and field names are required)
- Available speakers: ryan, serena, vivian, aiden, eric, dylan, uncle_fu, ono_anna, sohee
- Available languages: english, spanish, chinese, japanese, korean
- Keep each text segment under 200 words for best audio quality
- Alternate between speakers naturally
- Include an intro and outro
- At the beginning each speaker must introduce themselves

Format (copy exactly — text goes after the metadata fields):

--- 01
speaker: [speaker_name]
language: [language]

[What this person says goes here as plain text]

--- 02
speaker: [speaker_name]
language: [language]

[What this person says goes here as plain text]

Generate the necessary segments for a ~10 minute podcast episode.

At the end present this in plain text and make it available to download as a text file.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- Generic Template -->
    <div class="tts-card">
        <div class="prompt-header">
            <h3>🎯 Generic Podcast Prompt</h3>
            <button class="copy-btn" @onclick='() => CopyToClipboard("prompt-generic")'>📋 Copy</button>
        </div>
        <p class="prompt-desc">A customizable template — replace [YOUR TOPIC HERE] with any subject.</p>
        <div class="prompt-box" id="prompt-generic">Generate a podcast conversation script between two hosts about [YOUR TOPIC HERE].

Rules:
- Use exactly this format for each segment (the --- separator and field names are required)
- Available speakers: ryan, serena, vivian, aiden, eric, dylan, uncle_fu, ono_anna, sohee
- Available languages: english, spanish, chinese, japanese, korean
- Keep each text segment under 200 words for best audio quality
- Alternate between speakers naturally
- Include an intro and outro
- At the beginning each speaker must introduce themselves

Format (copy exactly — text goes after the metadata fields):

--- 01
speaker: [speaker_name]
language: [language]

[What this person says goes here as plain text]

--- 02
speaker: [speaker_name]
language: [language]

[What this person says goes here as plain text]

Generate 8-12 segments for a ~5 minute podcast episode.
Topic: [YOUR TOPIC HERE]</div>
    </div>

    <!-- Context-Based Template -->
    <div class="tts-card">
        <div class="prompt-header">
            <h3>📄 Context-Based — Generate from Existing Content</h3>
            <button class="copy-btn" @onclick='() => CopyToClipboard("prompt-context")'>📋 Copy</button>
        </div>
        <p class="prompt-desc">Paste this prompt along with an article, document, or any content you already have — the LLM will turn it into a podcast script.</p>
        <div class="prompt-box" id="prompt-context">Based on this content, generate a podcast conversation script between two or three hosts about this topic.

Rules:
- Use exactly this format for each segment (the --- separator and field names are required)
- Available speakers: ryan, serena, vivian, aiden, eric, dylan, uncle_fu, ono_anna, sohee
- Available languages: english, spanish, chinese, japanese, korean
- Keep each text segment under 200 words for best audio quality
- Alternate between speakers naturally
- Include an intro and outro

Format (copy exactly — text goes after the metadata fields):

--- 01
speaker: [speaker_name]
language: [language]

[What this person says goes here as plain text]

--- 02
speaker: [speaker_name]
language: [language]

[What this person says goes here as plain text]

Generate the necessary segments for a ~10 minute podcast episode.
At the beginning each speaker must introduce themselves.

Content:
[PASTE YOUR CONTENT HERE]</div>
    </div>

    <!-- English AI Topic -->
    <div class="tts-card">
        <div class="prompt-header">
            <h3>🤖 English — AI Agents in Software Development</h3>
            <button class="copy-btn" @onclick='() => CopyToClipboard("prompt-en-ai")'>📋 Copy</button>
        </div>
        <p class="prompt-desc">Two hosts discuss the impact of AI agents on coding and development workflows.</p>
        <div class="prompt-box" id="prompt-en-ai">Generate a podcast conversation script between two hosts about the future of AI agents in software development.

Rules:
- Use exactly this format for each segment (the --- separator and field names are required)
- Use speakers "ryan" and "serena" alternating
- Language: english
- Keep each text segment under 200 words for best audio quality
- Include an intro and outro
- Make it engaging, conversational, and informative
- At the beginning each speaker must introduce themselves

Format (copy exactly — text goes after the metadata fields):

--- 01
speaker: ryan
language: english

[intro text here]

--- 02
speaker: serena
language: english

[response text here]

Generate 10 segments for a ~5 minute podcast episode.
Topic: The future of AI agents in software development</div>
    </div>

    <!-- English Science Topic -->
    <div class="tts-card">
        <div class="prompt-header">
            <h3>🔬 English — Science & Technology News</h3>
            <button class="copy-btn" @onclick='() => CopyToClipboard("prompt-en-science")'>📋 Copy</button>
        </div>
        <p class="prompt-desc">A weekly science news roundup podcast with two co-hosts.</p>
        <div class="prompt-box" id="prompt-en-science">Generate a podcast conversation script for a weekly science and technology news roundup.

Rules:
- Use exactly this format for each segment (the --- separator and field names are required)
- Use speakers "aiden" and "vivian" alternating
- Language: english
- Keep each text segment under 200 words for best audio quality
- Cover 3-4 recent science/tech stories
- Include an intro, transitions between stories, and an outro
- Make it fun and accessible for a general audience
- At the beginning each speaker must introduce themselves

Format (copy exactly — text goes after the metadata fields):

--- 01
speaker: aiden
language: english

[intro text here]

--- 02
speaker: vivian
language: english

[response text here]

Generate 12 segments for a ~6 minute podcast episode.
Topic: This week in science and technology</div>
    </div>

    <!-- Spanish Topic -->
    <div class="tts-card">
        <div class="prompt-header">
            <h3>🇪🇸 Spanish — Inteligencia Artificial y el Futuro</h3>
            <button class="copy-btn" @onclick='() => CopyToClipboard("prompt-es-ai")'>📋 Copy</button>
        </div>
        <p class="prompt-desc">Podcast en español sobre IA y su impacto en la sociedad.</p>
        <div class="prompt-box" id="prompt-es-ai">Genera un guion de podcast conversacional entre dos presentadores sobre inteligencia artificial y su impacto en la sociedad.

Reglas:
- Usa exactamente este formato para cada segmento
- Usa los presentadores "ryan" y "serena" alternando
- Idioma: spanish
- Mantén cada segmento de texto bajo 200 palabras
- Incluye una intro y un cierre
- Hazlo conversacional, informativo y entretenido
- Al inicio cada presentador debe presentarse

Formato (copiar exactamente — el texto va después de los campos de metadatos):

--- 01
speaker: ryan
language: spanish

[texto de intro aquí]

--- 02
speaker: serena
language: spanish

[texto de respuesta aquí]

Genera 10 segmentos para un episodio de podcast de ~5 minutos.
Tema: El impacto de la inteligencia artificial en la vida cotidiana</div>
    </div>

    <!-- Interview Style -->
    <div class="tts-card">
        <div class="prompt-header">
            <h3>🎤 English — Interview Format</h3>
            <button class="copy-btn" @onclick='() => CopyToClipboard("prompt-en-interview")'>📋 Copy</button>
        </div>
        <p class="prompt-desc">A host interviews a guest expert — great for educational or deep-dive content.</p>
        <div class="prompt-box" id="prompt-en-interview">Generate a podcast script in interview format where a host interviews a guest expert about [YOUR TOPIC HERE].

Rules:
- Use exactly this format for each segment (the --- separator and field names are required)
- Use "ryan" as the host (curious, asks good questions)
- Use "serena" as the guest expert (knowledgeable, gives detailed answers)
- Language: english
- Keep each text segment under 200 words
- Start with the host introducing the guest
- End with a thank you and wrap-up
- The host should ask follow-up questions based on the guest's answers
- At the beginning each speaker must introduce themselves

Format (copy exactly — text goes after the metadata fields):

--- 01
speaker: ryan
language: english

[host introduces the guest and topic]

--- 02
speaker: serena
language: english

[guest responds]

Generate 10-12 segments for a ~5 minute interview.
Topic: [YOUR TOPIC HERE]</div>
    </div>

    <!-- Storytelling -->
    <div class="tts-card">
        <div class="prompt-header">
            <h3>📖 English — Storytelling / Narrative</h3>
            <button class="copy-btn" @onclick='() => CopyToClipboard("prompt-en-story")'>📋 Copy</button>
        </div>
        <p class="prompt-desc">A single narrator tells a compelling story — great for audiobook-style content.</p>
        <div class="prompt-box" id="prompt-en-story">Generate a podcast script for a storytelling episode with a single narrator.

Rules:
- Use exactly this format for each segment (the --- separator and field names are required)
- Use speaker "ryan" for all segments
- Language: english
- Keep each text segment under 150 words for natural pacing
- Tell a compelling story with a beginning, middle, and end
- Use vivid descriptions and engaging narration
- Include pauses between story beats (separate segments)

Format (copy exactly — text goes after the metadata fields):

--- 01
speaker: ryan
language: english

[opening narration]

--- 02
speaker: ryan
language: english

[story continues]

Generate 8-10 segments for a ~4 minute story.
Topic: [YOUR STORY TOPIC HERE]</div>
    </div>
</div>

@code {
    private async Task CopyToClipboard(string elementId)
    {
        await JS.InvokeVoidAsync("eval", $@"
            var el = document.getElementById('{elementId}');
            if (el) {{
                navigator.clipboard.writeText(el.innerText).then(function() {{
                    var btn = el.parentElement.querySelector('.copy-btn');
                    if (btn) {{ btn.innerText = '✓ Copied!'; setTimeout(function(){{ btn.innerText = '📋 Copy'; }}, 2000); }}
                }});
            }}
        ");
    }
}
